  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "e79add3f-3641-4d98-8b82-da1463898324",
    "name": "Finance Backend Api Documentation",
    "description": "# 💰 Finance Backend API Documentation\n\n## 📌 Overview\n\nThis collection contains APIs for a **microservices-based finance backend system** built using Spring Boot.\n\nThe system supports:\n\n- User management with roles (ADMIN, ANALYST, VIEWER)\n    \n- Financial records CRUD operations\n    \n- Filtering of financial data\n    \n- Dashboard analytics (summary, category-wise, trends)\n    \n- Role-based access control\n    \n- Input validation and error handling\n    \n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Architecture\n\nThe backend follows a **microservices architecture**:\n\n- **User Service** → Manages users and roles\n    \n- **Finance Service** → Handles financial records\n    \n- **Dashboard Service** → Provides aggregated analytics\n    \n- **Eureka Server** → Service discovery\n    \n- **OpenFeign** → Inter-service communication\n    \n\n---\n\n## 🔐 Authorization\n\nRole-based access control is implemented using request headers.\n\n### Required Header:\n\n```\nrole: ADMIN | ANALYST | VIEWER\n\n ```\n\n### Permissions:\n\n- **ADMIN** → Full access (CRUD operations)\n    \n- **ANALYST** → Read + analytics\n    \n- **VIEWER** → Read-only access\n    \n\n---\n\n## 📡 Available APIs\n\n### 🔹 Finance Service\n\n- Create record → `POST /records/create`\n    \n- Get records → `GET /records`\n    \n- Update record → `PUT /records/{id}`\n    \n- Delete record → `DELETE /records/{id}`\n    \n- Filter records → `GET /records/filter`\n    \n\n---\n\n### 🔹 Dashboard Service\n\n- Summary → `GET /dashboard/summary`\n    \n- Category-wise → `GET /dashboard/category`\n    \n- Recent activity → `GET /dashboard/recent`\n    \n- Monthly trends → `GET /dashboard/monthly`\n    \n\n---\n\n## 🧪 Sample Data\n\nUse the following JSON to test:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"amount\": 5000,\n  \"type\": \"INCOME\",\n  \"category\": \"Salary\",\n  \"date\": \"2026-04-03\",\n  \"description\": \"Monthly salary\",\n  \"userId\": 1\n}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ Error Handling\n\nThe system returns structured error responses:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Validation failed\",\n  \"status\": 400\n}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n## 🗄️ Data Persistence\n\n- PostgreSQL is used for storing data\n    \n- Each microservice maintains its own database\n    \n- Finance Service stores `userId` instead of full user object (microservices best practice)\n    \n\n---\n\n## 📌 Assumptions\n\n- Role is passed via request header (simplified authentication)\n    \n- Services are independently deployable\n    \n- No shared database between services\n    \n\n---\n\n## 🚀 How to Use\n\n1. Start all services\n    \n2. Add role header in requests\n    \n3. Use provided endpoints to test functionality\n    \n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Purpose\n\nThis collection demonstrates backend design, API structure, access control, validation, and microservices communication for a finance dashboard system.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "42641318"
